<br>
It was another great day for HF!!  We came away after a fight with the great Faydedar and another of our druids now has their leafbblower!  Congratulations Tweniel!  We set up and took him down with 17 people, and no deaths!   HF 1, Faydedar 0.   Thank you to Fadien and Siiyan for leading this raid so successfully.<br>
<br>
We then headed off to Chardok.  Everyone was working together as a cohesive team, and we went in and eventually killed some royal butt.<br>
 <br>
We had one setback that was just a matter of technique and timing, opening a locked door and getting people through before they fell through the floor, one mob dropped and brought back the King's room and we had a wipe out--we'll know better next time.  One thing about disaster, it shows your 'metal' and it also finds you new friends.  <br>
<br>
Please take a moment to post on Pantheons MB about Pixius who was a 'prince among men' helping us to put our game face back on and plunge back into the challenge.  <br>
<br>
After the CR and Forbain who was instrumental in getting Darkrain coffins and having him summon our lifeless forms the clerics had us back up and running down to seek our revenge.  It was wonderful to see how people concentrated and followed the assist call--good job people!<br>
 <br>
Going back in with 19 people, two clerics came away with the singed scroll from the King for their epic!  Congratulations Galastrielle and Saelina!  Lithya and Repper also came away with Argent Protectors, an Argent Defender and Iksar Skin Gloves went to the guild bank for later distribution and Galastrielle won the Etched Signet for research of a level 60 spell.  HF 2, Overking 1.    Thank you again to Siiyan for leading us so skillfully and willingly into the jaws of death to come out on top.<br>
<br>
Thank you to all of Hearts Fury members for showing up to make such a great day and great leaps towards finishing some of our much-needed epics!<br>
